## Brewer helped give Petey the win.

9) Shane Helms DQ Lizmark Jr.
## Lizmark fouled Helms for the DQ. Marco helped run off Treachery post match.
&& Nine matches probably means three shows. They now have five episodes to air, and no defined air date. Last time, they were saying late January. This taping, they were just saying 'soon'. AAA TV (FRI) 02/04/2011 Arena Naucalpan [http://www.luchalibreaaa.com/cronicanaucalpan04feb.html AAA, http://www.flickr.com/photos/blackterry/sets/72157625855947495/with/5418075333/ Black Terry Jr. (flickr), http://miluchalibre.com/2011/02/ha-muerto-el-rey-de-reyes/ Mi Lucha Libre (3)]Attendance: 2800

4) Electroshock b Heavy Metal
## Earlier in the night, Metal challenged Electroshock to make this a best of five series, with the loser losing his hair. Electroshock quickly agreed, then doubted Metal would last the whole series. Electroshock is now calling himself a High Definition Luchador. For this match, Metal had the woman and mini with him from his recent vignettes. The mini tried bringing in a guitar to help, but Electroshock took it and used it for the win.

## Park went for a top rope splash, Mesias got his knees up, and hit his own top rope splash for the win. Rudos (including Decnnis, who suffered a head injury) attacked post match, and Cuervo ran out for the save. Hints here that Mesias and the Sect may be friends again.

## Charly had Parka set up for El Pozo again, Zorro returned to cane Charly, and Parka picked up the pin.

Bucanero tried faking a foul in the third fall, but it didn't work. Perico snuck in to foul Maximo, which worked last week, but Maximo moved and Bucanero was fouled by his own parrot. Maximo got the big win. Bucanero was very sad.

AAA TV (FRI) 03/04/2011 Gimnasio Miguel Hidalgo, Puebla, Puebla [http://www.luchalibreaaa.com/tcarlitopasa.html AAA, http://www.flickr.com/photos/blackterry/sets/72157626221390666/with/5508724392/ Black Terry Jr. (flickr), http://miluchalibre.com/2011/03/carlito-obtiene-su-pase/ Mi Lucha Libre (4), http://www.record.com.mx/luchalibre/2011-03-04/carlito-gana-pase-rey-de-reyes Record]Attendance: 2500
1) Fénix, Lolita, Mari Apache b Billy Boy, Jennifer Blake, Sexy Star
## Fenix was the mystery luchador, Lolita continues to fill in for Fabi Apache. Mari Apache sentoned Sexy Star for the win. Tirantes attacked Mari after the match, then was ready for Apache when he ran in and bloodied the older man. Tirantes accepted a match with Apache, which should take place at Rey de Reyes (and probably won't be a singles match.)
2) Charly Manson, Escoria, Nygma b Espíritu, Joe Lider, Nicho el Millionario
## Charly threw powder in Joe Lider's face, leading to the Bizarro win. Bizarros beat up Joe Lider & Nicho after the match, but Escoria would not let his partners attack Espiritu. While that was being sorted out, Zorro attacked Charly.
3) Electroshock b Heavy Metal [vale todo]
## Maniacos interference - still apparently unwelcome by Metal - backfired this time, giving Electroshock the win. The Maniacos brought out a bottle for Metal to use on Electro. He refused, but Electro stole and hit Metal himself. This great Hombre Contra Hombre five match series has now had every match so far end by someone else getting involved. Electroshock leads 2-1.
4) Carlito Caribbean Cool b Jack Evans, Decnnis, Ozz [Rey de Reyes, semifinal]
## Crowd was way behind Carlito. Carlito pinned Ozz after a swinging neckbreaker, Jack got Decnnis with a bridging pin, Carlito got Jack with the backcracker. After the match, Konnan offered Jennifer and Sexi to Carlito to get him to join La Sociedad. Carlito agreed, saying all Mexican women are ugly (having no idea who Sexi is, I guess), that Mexico is a horrible place, and he'll be on the first plane to leave after winning Rey de Reyes. Carlito specifically wants to take out Mesias, but had issues with LA Park later.
5) Cuervo, El Mesías, Extreme Tiger b LA Park, Silver King, Último Gladiador
## Carlito tried to interfere, only for everyone in La Sociedad and AAA to counter-interfere. Post match included a confrontation between the four Rey de Reyes finalists.

CMLL (SUN) 03/13/2011 Arena México [CMLL, http://estrellasdelring.blogspot.com/2011/03/la-sombra-nuevo-campeon-historico-nwa.html Estrellas del Ring, http://www.record.com.mx/luchalibre/2011-03-13/infierno-ensombrecido Record]
** Fan Appreciation Show, March (Sun)Attendance: 9500
1) Camaleón, Robin b Cholo, Zayco
2) Inquisidor, Mortiz, Rayo Tapatío I, Rayo Tapatío II b Bobby Zavala, Dragón Lee, Hijo del Signo, Hombre Bala Jr. [cibernetico]
## Veterans won, but not without some controversy. First two out were Zavala (Mortiz spanish fly), Hombre Bala (Rayo II), leading the rookies down 4-2. Signo & Lee eliminated Mortiz, but then Signo fell next. That left Rush's brother versus both Tapatios and Inquisidor. Dragon Lee spectacularly eliminated Inquisidor with a SSP. Tapatios started using rudo tactics on the young tecnico, but Lee still beat Rayo I. It looked like he might get Rayo II as well, but Inquisidor got involved, and Rayo II stole Dragon Lee's mask to set up the winning cradle.
3) Fuego, Metro, Sagrado b Dr. X, Shigeo Okumura, Yoshihashi
## Rudos took the first, tecs the last two. Sagrado and Okumura continue to feud.
4) El Alebrije, Olímpico, Psicosis b Averno, Ephesto, Rey Bucanero [semifinal]
5) Felino, Mr. Niebla, Negro Casas b Terrible, Texano Jr., Volador Jr. [semifinal]
6) Felino, Mr. Niebla, Negro Casas b El Alebrije, Olímpico, Psicosis [final]
## Cuije and Zacarias fought during this match. Looks like Niebla and Felino won it clean for their team.
7) La Sombra b Mephisto  (c) [NWA WELTER]
## Tecnico won the first, rudo won the second, tecnico won the third. Springboard flip 'rana (Dragonrana) for the win in about 30 minutes.

GALLI (SUN) 03/13/2011 Addison Communinty Center, Addison, IllinoisAttendance: 175
1) Ovirload b Joey Marx
## Marx is still really good. Ovirload is a masked dark skinned man, with manager JC Smallz. Marx was about to do a top rope move when Ovirload's manager tripped him. Ovirload dropped Marx with a reverse stunner for the win. Good opener. Ovirload has the worst music, only fans of German noise bands could appreciate it.
2) G2L, Rey Fuego b Fúnebre, Sepultura
## I'm sure I have at least two names wrong in this match; undercard was changed around quite a bit from what was listed. Fuego is a dancing flyer in the mold of Zumbi, G2L (can't be right) is a ex-convict who's a tecnico but still in touch with his convict roots, Sepultura was a bald man. Disjoined match - I'd look away for a second, and the other team would be in control when I looked back, for no apparent reason - but lots of action. Fuego got his trunks pulled on a sunset flip spot, but recovered to pin Sepultura on a bridging cover. 10 minuet match.
3) Ace Martino, Diego Corleone, Jack ONeil b Alex Olsen, Matt Knicks, Nikita Allanov
## When Matt and Alex came bouncing out to the ring and Nikita sternly walked behind them, I was sure there was a turn coming. There was, just the wrong guy. Knicks and Josh? had a miscommunication that led to Knicks shoving Alex into the rudos attack, starting a long face in peril bit. After a lot of triple teaming and chicanery, Alex made the hot tag to Nikita. Things broke down from there. Triple stunners by the tecnicos looked to set up dives, but Matt crotched Alex on the top rope, then fouled Nikita just as he was going to get his hands on Diego. Diego covered for the win, and Knicks joined the rudos post match. About 11 minutes.
4) Bryce Benjamin, Mason Conrad, Valentino b Furia Roja, Golden Star, Guardián
## Rudos represent the Underground, but Guardian has their (Bryce's) title belt. Guardian is a lot better than the last time I've seen him; he was OK, now he's quite good. Most everyone looked good in this match, built around Bryce wanting to fight Guardain but not head to head. Rudos were no match for the tecnicos near the end, tecnicos almost slaughtering them, when a ref distraction allowed Ovirload to slip and punch Guardian with knucks. Conrad picked up the pin. GALLI promoter Carlos Robles suspended all four rudos and their manager from the next show (in a couple weeks) for this vile act of cheating. 11 minutes.
5) Discovery, Máscarita Dorada b Pierrothito, Yakuza
## it's the Mascarita Dorada/Pierrothito show, it's up to the other guys just to keep up. Discovery and Yakzua did enough. Pierrothito was not only vexed by his diminutive opponent, but by the microphone (holding it to close and breaking up every time he talked.) Probably not a lot you haven't seen if you've seen these two, and not a full on crazy match, but still a very good one. First three fall match of the night, rudos taking the first, tecnicos rallying back for the second and third. Didn't realize Dorada and Octagoncito are using the same exact cradle finish until Dorada used it here to win. Pierrothito and Dorada talked about a title vs title match after this one.
6) 450 Hammet, Samuray del Sol, Shiima Xion b Emperador, Low Rider, Pesadilla
## Low Rider & Pesadilla wore Perros del Mal shirts. Samuray had a I [heart] DTU shirt, and Xion was wearing a EXTREMO one. Another match where a lot of people looked really good. Low Rider was the standout to me, a great guy at interacting with the crowd and showing personality, besides the other excellent work. Very high on him after seeing this match. Just like the semimain, rudos took the first, tecnicos came back to win the second (maybe a too over complicated finish here), big dive train (Xion last) in the third, and all the tecnicos did 450 splashes on all rudos for the win. Funebre helped the rudos attack the tecnicos post match; Samurai's mask was pulled off and ripped up. Tecnicos from earlier in the show made the save. Joey Marx slid face first into the ring at full speed, but his pants must've got caught on something, because he slid half the way out of them, mooning the crowd. Everyone in the ring just about died laughing for a moment about it, before more post match challenges.
&& bottom rope broke during intermission, thanks to kids jumping on it. Was right at the end of intermission too, which turned out to be about the middle of it. Everything was working by the time the fifth match started.

AAA TV (FRI) 03/18/2011 Plaza de Toros San Marcos, Aguascalientes, Aguascalientes [@lomejordelalucha, http://www.luchalibreaaa.com/reydereyes2011cronica.html AAA, http://miluchalibre.com/2011/03/tirantitos-no-gana-pero-se-desquita/ Mi Lucha Libre (1), http://miluchalibre.com/2011/03/la-parka-humillado-por-los-bizarros/ Mi Lucha Libre (2), http://miluchalibre.com/2011/03/muerden-los-perros-a-psycho-y-dr-wagner-jr/ Mi Lucha Libre (3), http://miluchalibre.com/2011/03/el-zorro-continua-su-reinado/ Mi Lucha Libre (4), http://miluchalibre.com/2011/03/electro-cae-ante-heavy/ Mi Lucha Libre (5), http://miluchalibre.com/2011/03/viva-el-rey-xtreme-tiger/ Mi Lucha Libre (6), http://www.record.com.mx/luchalibre/2011-03-19/xtreme-tiger-es-rey-de-triple Record]
** Rey de Reyes, 2011
1) Gran Apache, Mari Apache, Octagoncito, Pimpinela Escarlata b Hijo del Tirantes, Mini Histeria, Sexy Star, Yuriko
## Fabi got involved to help the tecncios win. Jennifer attacked her with a chair, and Fabi was strechered out again.
2) Billy el Malo, Cibernético, Escoria, Nygma b Jack Evans, Joe Lider, La Parka, Nicho el Millionario
## Billy was the non-surprise surprise. Parka bled a lot. Cibernetico used knuckles on Parka to win. Bizarros beat up Parka after the match, unmasking him and putting on a Bizarro mask. Bizarros threatened to light Parka on fire, but Nicho stoppped Cibernetico and Psycho Circus made the save.
3) Damián 666, el Hijo del Perro Aguayo, Halloween, Súper Crazy b Dr. Wagner Jr., Monster Clown, Murder Clown, Psycho Clown
## Crazy brawl. Super Crazy dived off something very high. Perro hit Wagner with a chair shot and top rope double stomped him for the win. Perros took the Clown's masks after the match.
4) Zorro  (c) b Charly Manson [AAA MEGA]
## Interference from Billy and Jennifer. Zorro finally took out Billy with the superkick and gave Charly a facebuster for the win.
5) Heavy Metal b Electroshock [hair, bull terrier]
## randomly, a bull terrier match. Electroshock finally took out the mini and woman. Electroshock hit Pepe Casas in the third, but Metal hit Electroshock with a guitar, again, for the win. Konnan, Chessman Super Crazy and Halloween appeared post match to invite Metal into La Sociedad. When Metal considered this (and how he turned it down last time), Chessman superkicked him and the rudos beat up Metal. Electroshock, made the save and got clobbered too. Metal and Electroshock may now be friends.
6) Extreme Tiger b El Mesías, LA Park, Carlito [Rey de Reyes]
## Mesias and Park brawled outside until Mesias jumped off something very high and put Park thru a table, getting them both counted out. Carlito was accidentally tripped off the top rope by Piero, and Tiger landed a 450 splash for the win. (I hope that looks better than it sounds.) Joaquin Roldan and Dr. Wagner awarded him the sword for winning.

CMLL (FRI) 03/18/2011 Arena México [http://loscoliseinos.blogspot.com/2011/03/homenaje-dos-leyendasy-un-gitano-horuz.html Cesar, http://estrellasdelring.blogspot.com/2011/03/sin-sorpresas-en-el-homenaje-dos.html CMLL, http://www.mediotiempo.com/mas-deportes/noticias/2011/03/19/pelones-super-porky-y-maximo MT, http://www.record.com.mx/luchalibre/2011-03-18/averno-retiene-cetro-con-marrullerias Record (5)]
** Dos Leyendas: Angel Blanco & Salvador LutterothAttendance: 10500
1) Astral, Eléctrico, Último Dragóncito CO Pequeño Nitro, Pequeño Violencia, Pierrothito
## Astral replaced Bam Bam. Rudos took the first. Tecnicos took the last two, winning the third via dives. Astral looked bad in the clip on radiocmll.com.
2) Diamante, Metro, Stuka Jr. DQ Euforia, Raziel, Shigeo Okumura
## Tecnicos took the first, Euforia ripped off Stuka's mask for the straight fall loss. Tecnicos brought a Fabian el Gitano shirt to the ring and pointed to the sky. Luchadors filled the ring for a moment of applause for Fabina el Gitano after the match.
3) Atlantis, Dragón Rojo Jr., Último Guerrero b Ángel de Oro, Blue Panther, Valiente
## Rudos took the first, tecnicos took the second, rudos took the third - while Valiente dove on UG, the other two tecnicos ran straight into Atlantidas. Angel Blanco's family was honored after the match. Horuz unveiled a new mask, resembling his grandfather's mask. It appears he'll be sticking with the Horuz name.
4) Felino, Mr. Niebla, Negro Casas b La Sombra, Rush, Toscano
## Toscano was wearing a "Fabian" armband. Tecnicos took the first, rudos the second, Niebla legdropped Monito in the third, Sombra hit a big tope, minis brawled, and the rudos took it.
5) Averno  (c) b Máscara Dorada [NWA MIDDLE]
## Dorada's fireman's carry powerbomb in the first, Devil's Wings in the second. Long third fall, with Mephisto tripping Dorada up and Averno sneaking in a foul for the win. Black Warrior, reintroduced to the crowd before the match, attacked Averno and unmasked him after this match.
6) Terrible, Texano b Máximo, Súper Porky [hair]
## tecnicos won the first fall in seconds, rudos won the second, though only after nearly being beat by a Porky splash. Two different dive sequences in the third fall. Maximo eliminated Terrible and Texano eliminated Porky at the same time. Texano escaped the kiss cradle (thanks to Terrible distracting the ref) and dropped Maximo with Tornado Texano for the win. Maximo and Porky got shaved in the ring, with many of their CMLL family members (Robin, Goya, Brazo de Oro, La Mascara I think) standing with them.

<BR>In between matches, Dr. Wagner tried to call out the surprise wrestler for tonight's show, but instead got Tito Santana. Tito, relating a message from Konnan, slapped Wagner. Wagner laid him out with a Wagner Driver, then vowed to take care of the new guy if he's not with AAA.

## Chessman pinned Electroshock with a 450 splash. Maniacos attacked Electroshock after the match and Heavy Metal ran in to make the save. Metal explained it was so he didn't owe anything to Electroshock for saving him previously.
4) Drago, Joe Lider, La Parka b Charly Manson, Cibernético, Escoria
## Drako is a green lizard thing who's moves bare a striking similarity to Gato Eveready. Cibernetico, Dorian and Konnan all tried to recruit him before the match, but Drago dropkicked Konnan and dived onto the Milicia guys outside the ring. Drago picked up the win with green mist, a tornillo onto Charly and was generally treated like a big deal. After the match, Parka told Cibernetico that he'd seen Cibernetico's recent videos, and stole something form his house to pay him back. Hope it's not his dog. Drago threatened to burn Cibernetico too.
5) Damián 666, Halloween, Hijo del Lizmark, X-Fly b Dr. Wagner Jr., Monster Clown, Murder Clown, Psycho Clown
## Wagner was wearing a combo Psycho Clown/Dr. Wagner mask. Halloween fouled Monster Clown for the win. Rudos went for the masks, Jack, Lider, Drako and Parka all ran in for the save.

IWRG (SUN) 04/24/2011 Arena Naucalpan [http://alfilodelring.blogspot.com/2011/04/arena-naucalpan-24-de-abril-del-2011.html Al Filo del Ring, http://www.flickr.com/photos/blackterry/sets/72157626447412815/ Black Terry Jr. (flickr), http://estrellasdelring.blogspot.com/2011/04/los-psycho-circus-nuevos-campeones-de.html Estrellas del Ring, http://miluchalibre.com/2011/04/aaa-sigue-enrachada-en-la-guerra-de-empresas/ Mi Lucha Libre (1-6), http://miluchalibre.com/2011/04/psycho-circus-destronan-a-maniacos/ Mi Lucha Libre (7), http://www.record.com.mx/luchalibre/2011-04-25/intercambio-de-parejas Record, http://www.thegladiatores.com/?p=5119 The Gladiatores]
1) La Chiva, Mini Charly Manson, Sexy Lady NC Fresero Jr., Ludark Shaitan, Máscarita Sagrada 2007
## Instead of Jennifer and Lolita (elsewhere), Mini Charly Manson and Mascarita Sagrada were added to the card. We haven't seen the AAA Sagrada in so long, I forgot there was one. This Chiva, who's been on spots shows for at least a couple years, is all white and doesn't have the soccer gear. No contest after Los Maniacos (or at least Silver King & Lider) ran in and beat up everyone except Fresero, who helped them. Most notable, the Ludark's face was covered in blood. There was some suggestion on Twitter that the rudos excessively roughed up Ludark here. Electroshock finally made the save.
2) Máscara Año 2000 Jr., Veneno b Paranoiko, Violento Jack [Guerra de Empresas, quarterfinal]
## Violento Jack's team was representing DTU, but since Violento Jack is now feuding with DTU, he turned on his partner for the loss. Paranoiko replaced Crazy Boy.
3) Hijo del Pirata Morgan, Lizmark Jr. DCO Hijo del Dr. Wagner Jr., Trauma I [Guerra de Empresas, quarterfinal]
## Pirata Morgan & Lizmark Jr. were representing the Perros del Mal; Pirata Morgan (not a Perro) replaced Halloween. Wagner/Trauma were the Juniors team, though Trauma I hasn't wrestled in that promotion.
4) Nicho el Millionario, Pimpinela Escarlata b Black Terry, El Brazo [Guerra de Empresas, quarterfinal]
## Pimpi replaced Tiger. Black Terry replaced Negro Navarro; I think they were the ex-UWA team.
5) Nicho el Millionario, Pimpinela Escarlata b Máscara Año 2000 Jr., Veneno [Guerra de Empresas, final]
## Team AAA wins.
6) Halloween, La Parka Jr. DQ Cibernético, Electroshock [Relevos Increíbles]
## Charly Manson was detained, so Halloween replaced him. Cibernetico fouled Parka in front of the ref for the DQ.
7) Joe Lider, Silver King, Último Gladiador  (c) L Monster Clown, Murder Clown, Psycho Clown and Bestia 666, Damián 666, X-Fly and Oficial 911, Oficial AK47, Oficial Fierro [cage, IWRG IC TRIOS]
## Oficials left first, followed by Silver and UG. Lider was outnumbered and beat up by the other trios. Silver & UG came back and fought the Clowns, allowing the Perros to slip out. Last two left in were Zombie and Gladiador, Lider swung a chair, and accidentally hit his partners. Psycho Circus are champions. Too bad Vampiro wasn't there for them to shove again. Maniacos turned on Lider after the match and Lider made the save. Perros attacked the Clowns as well.

2) Arkángel de la Muerte, Loco Max, Skándalo b Ángel Azteca, Ángel de Plata, Pegasso
## Rudos took 1/3.
3) Delta b Rey Escorpión [Forjando un Idolo, quarterfinal]
## Crowd got into this match. Rey Escorpion tried to cheat again, but Ultimo Guerrero stopped him and Delta eventually took the win. Ultimo Guerrero and Rey Escorpion had real problems after this one, shoving each other on (and off) the ramp.
4) Pólvora b Hijo del Signo [Forjando un Idolo, quarterfinal]
## Hijo del Signo was the last Group Alfa (Negro Casas) member standing. He lost, and Polvora becomes the second group Delta (Blue Panther) member to get thru.

## Bonus match, added midweek (but not publicized.) Probably not airing.
6) Negro Casas, Rey Bucanero, Terrible b Máximo, Súper Porky, Toscano
## Rudos won, but Terrible & Bucanero turned on Zacarias and Negro Casas post match. Members of Fuerza TRT do not want anything to do with other rudos.
7) Averno, Ephesto, Último Guerrero DQ Blue Panther, La Máscara, Máscara Dorada
## Rudos won in straight falls, with La Mascara angrily ripping off Averno's mask in the second fall. More mask/mask challenges.

5) Sol I, Sol II b Oriental  (c) [LLUSA TAG]
## The Sols were the people getting involved in Oriental & Tinieblas Jr. matches previously. Tinieblas was not there, so Oriental took them both on and lost. Mr. Aguila made the save after the match (Invasors sticking together! probably not.) They were able to unmask one of Sol, who turned out to be Tinieblas Jr. Oriental could not believe it. After, it was announced the tag team titles were vacant because they changed hands in a handicap match.
6) Rocky Romero, Súper Nova b PR Flyer, San Juan Kid
## sounds like a very good match. In an unrelated skit between matches, Rebecca Reyes turned heel on Mini Halloween, claiming she had actually married him to divorce him and get half of his money (!?!?), but it turned out Mini Halloween had not actually signed the marriage papers and instead filed a restraining order.
7) Jon Rekon, Petey Williams b Jay Lethal, Magno
## Lethal was wearing his Macho Man gear, a surprise partner since Romero & Nova had just wrestled. Rekon dropped Magno with a Samoan Drop and Petey picked up the win. Petey got in a shoving fight with a planted fan after the match.
8) RJ Brewer b Psicosis II
## presumbably Lizmark's challenge match for Brewer. Poor Psicosis can't win a singles match anywhere!
9) Lizmark Jr.  (c) b Rocky Romero [LLUSA HEAVY]
## Rocky challenged Lizmark to prove he was tough by defending his title. Said to be a good match, Lizmark winning clean.

Elegido & Argos picked up the win, La Milicia ran in, and Pimpi, Laredo, Aero and Sugi ran them off. Guapito appeared - it seems likes we've missed a skit here, because he talked about being put in charge by Konnan (to run off the AAA tecnicos) and Super Fly agreed to support this new war. It looks like this could've set up a 6v6 match, but I'm not sure if it's happening or happening at TripleMania.

## Halloween replaced Bestia 666. X-Fly interfered in the match freely, and he and Charly appeared to remember they feuded last year. No explanation of why the teams changed, but that sets up precedent for down the road. Dark Family got involved late, as did Bestia. With Espiritu's distraction of Escoria setting up a Halloween's spear. Perro added a chair assisted double stomp to pick up the win. Psycho Circus attacked the Perros, and all four teams brawled to close out the show.
&& The first four matches were all changed in position.

CMLL (FRI) 06/17/2011 Arena México [http://loscoliseinos.blogspot.com/2011/06/el-juicio-final-es-un-exito-las.html Cesar, CMLL, http://cmllgaceta.wordpress.com/2011/06/18/destruida-la-maldicion-alvarado-%E2%80%9Cla-mascara-triunfador-absoluto%E2%80%9D/ CMLL Gaceta (6), http://estrellasdelring.blogspot.com/2011/06/adios-averno-bienvenido-renato-ruiz.html Estrellas del Ring, http://www.record.com.mx/luchalibre/2011-06-18/alfa-y-charly-ganan-en-fui Record (1-5), http://www.record.com.mx/luchalibre/2011-06-18/destapa-la-mascara-averno Record (6), http://superluchas.net/2011/06/17/cobertura-cmll-el-juicio-final-2011-17-de-junio-de-2011-%c2%a1averno-pierde-la-mascara-%c2%a1renato-ruiz-es-averno/ SuperLuchas]
** Juicio Final, 2011Attendance: 13500
1) Metro, Stuka Jr. b Shigeo Okumura, Yoshihashi
## tecnicos take fall 1/3.
2) Rey Bucanero, Terrible, Texano b Brazo de Plata, Hijo del Fantasma, Valiente
## TRT takes fall 1/3, with a superbomb on Super Porky to take the match.
3) Diamante, Hijo del Signo, Negro Casas b Blue Panther, Fuego, Pólvora [Forjando un Idolo]
## Team Negro Casas took the last two falls. They advance to next week's final, a bit of redemption after neither Diamante nor Signo made the semifinals in the individual version of this tournament. Fuego & Polvora continue to get approval for their team work.
4) Atlantis, Delta, Guerrero Maya Jr. DQ Ángel de Oro, Rey Escorpión, Último Guerrero [Forjando un Idolo]
## Guerrero Maya worked against Ultimo Guerrero in the opening mat work and impressed. Straight falls for the Atlantis crew. Big tease of UG vs Atlantis in the second, Atlantis got UG in the Atlantida, and Rey Escorpion fouled him for the DQ. Atlantis & UG were fine after the match, but Oro & Ultimo Guerrero were angry at Rey Escorpion again. Escorpion kissed UG's boots to apologize. Team Shocker/Atlantis goes onto next week's final.
5) La Sombra, Rush, Strong Man b Mephisto, Mr. Niebla, Shinsuke Nakamura
## Tecnicos took 2/3. Mephisto was wearing an Averno/Mephisto fused mask. Tirantes refereed this match, but not the main event.
6) La Máscara b Averno [mask]
## Babe Richard was the referee. Big entrances for both men. Mascara had Brazo de Oro in his corner, Averno had both Ephesto and Mephisto walk with him to the ring, though Ephesto went to the back during the match. Other wrestlers were watching the match, Shocker most visibly. Mascara started the match with the Brazo de Oro/Mascara split mask he'd worn in some of the vignettes, but also started the match with a tope towards Averno. Averno was ready, and hit Mascara with a metal object, causing Mascara to bleed. Quick first fall for Averno via Devil's Wings, and Mascara snuck out the second fall with a small package. Long third fall, both guys surviving each other's and their own usual finishers, including Mascara kicking after a super Devil's Wings. Mascara finally got Averno with two Devil's Wings and then the campana for the win. Crowd was way behind Averno to start, but at least some of them came around to Mascara by the second fall - mostly a female supporters. Ephesto & Mephesto unmasked Averno, who is Renato Ruiz Cortez, 34 years old, 16 years a wrestler. Averno gave credit to Mascara for being the better man on this day and left without giving interviews to the press. He's got a mohawk, partially dyed white. Mascara celebrates with Brazo de Oro, Maximo and Super Brazo.
&& Referee Rafa el Maya was shown at the show, now out of the hospital. CMLL was back to having two referees in the ring for matches. Attendance guesses range from 80% to 'all the tickets were sold!'

AAA TV (SAT) 06/18/2011 Palacio de los Deportes, Iztacalco, Distrito Federal [http://espaldasplanasradio07.blogspot.com/2011/06/triplemania-xix_19.html Espaldas Planas, http://estrellasdelring.blogspot.com/2011/06/wagner-jr-vencio-rvd-jeff-jarrett-nuevo.html Estrellas del Ring, http://miluchalibre.com/2011/06/asi-perdio-mesias-su-cabellera/ Mi Lucha Libre (8), http://rderudooficial.blogspot.com/2011/06/triplemania-xix-la-park-rapa-al-mesias.html R de Rudo, http://www.record.com.mx/luchalibre/2011-06-19/se-consagra-jarrett-megacampeon Record (1-7, 9), http://www.record.com.mx/luchalibre/2011-06-19/la-park-rapo-mesias Record (8), http://www.thegladiatores.com/?p=5693 The Gladiadtores]
** TripleMania XIXAttendance: 17900
1) Aerostar, Argos, Fénix, Sugi b Dark Dragón, Decnnis, Tigre Cota, Tito Santana
## Dark Match
2) Cinthia Moreno, Fabi Apache, Lolita, Mari Apache b Angelina Love, Mickie James, Sexy Star, Velvet Sky
## Mickie kissed Fabi, kicked her low, and DDTed her for the pin.
3) Electroshock, Heavy Metal, Joe Lider b Chessman, Silver Kain, Último Gladiador [TLC]
## Electroshock replaced Nicho. Electroshock in for Nicho. With many people bleeding, Metal was wiped out injured. Nicho ran in to take his place - but was then stopped and suspended by Joaquin Roldan. No run ins! Tecnicos still end up winning by pinfall (Electroshock on Chessman) - nothing to grab in this table match.
4) Billy el Malo, Charly Manson, Cibernético, Escoria b Drago, La Parka, Octagón, Ozz
## Taboo turned up in the late stages of the match, holding La Parka's kid - the one with the broken leg that started all of this - hostage. Parka was distracted and chokeslammed by Cibernetico for the pin. Taboo let the kid go (he went to his dad), and it was revealed Taboo is actually Parka's brother. (He legit is.) Probably responsible for passing on the x-rays to Cibernetico way back when.
5) Extreme Tiger, Jack Evans  (c) b Abyss, Mr. Anderson [AAA TAG, cage]
## Extreme Tiger did a cage dive on Abyss, then escaped. Anderson was next out. Jack powerbombed Abyss off the cage into thumbtacks to retain the tag titles.
6) Damián 666, Halloween, X-Fly b Monster Clown, Murder Clown, Psycho Clown [AAA TRIOS, final]
## X-Fly in for Perro, as previously announced. Damian was powerbombed into something that exploded, but the Perros still managed to win. Halloween gives Psycho a suepr Death Valley Driver thru a table for the pin.
7) Jeff Jarrett b Zorro  (c) [AAA MEGA]
## Jeff used or tried to use tortillas, powder, a guitar, and his wife to help him win, but eventually got the cane and used that on Zorro for the win. Zorro looked out of shape and we probably won’t be seeing him again for a while.
8) LA Park b El Mesías [hair, mask]
## Change of order! Pierroth (still wheelchair bound, but in his mask) appears to enter with LA Park. Hijo de LA Park is LA Park's second.

Long match, taking us past midnight. After multiple tables were broken, many chair shots, blood, and Park's mask ripped, Mesias accidentally kicks Piero, and Park uses brass knucks for the win. Mesias was quickly shaved in the ring.

Marisela Pena threw a drink at LA Park at one point, and Park taunted her after the match.
9) Dr. Wagner Jr. b Rob Van Dam [AAA LA]
## Dr. Wagner had a traditional Mexican musical performance and is wearing the flag colors. Rob Van Dam's name was spelled wrong. Dr. Wagner III is with his father.

These two got plenty of time. RVD survived the Wagner Driver, but felt to a hanging DDT. Wagner got the new belt and celebrated with the AAA tecnicos.

Four hour show. Looooong show.

Nicho was angry AAA would treat an original member of AAA this way, after he's given so much of his body to the company. Nicho said he was angry AAA gave his name to someone else, someone not nearly as good as him, when he left. Nicho talked about his son, and said he'd be forced to find work in another promotion if they suspended him without pay.

IWL (SUN) 07/03/2011 Deportivo Tlalli, Tlalnepantla, Estado De México
0) Jorge Kebrada, Mercurio XD, Yago vs Andy Boy, Dragosth, Golden
1) Veneno b Emo Extreme
## Stream went out during the match, but Veneno is said to have won.
2) Cerebro Maligno, Epitafio, Fantasma de la Ópera, Sepulcro b Amenaza Infernal Jr., Epidemia, Niño de Fuego, Químico Jr.
## Match was listed as Epidemia, Heavy Boy vs Centinela, Quimico Jr. When the stream returned, the tecnicos here were being beat up by the rudos. The rudos were all part of a new Fantamsa led faction, ATM, fighting management (as rudos, I think.) Rudos had Trolli with them and won this match. Like all the rest of the matches on this show, this was one fall. Infernal Jr. sure looked looked and wrestled like a masked Mad Man Pondo, though that never came into play.
3) Daga b Heavy Boy
## Daga, in street clothes with his title match, was out talking about the three way next and wanting to be in bigger matches. Fantasma de la Opera brought out new ATM member Heavy Boy to challenge him. Daga won the impromptu match.
4) Mike Segura b Naruto, Pesadilla [IWL INTERNET, #1 Contenders]
## Naruto was a replacement for Low Rider. Elimination match, with Pesdailla going out first and Naruto taking a superbomb thru a table for...a two count, then being immediately pinned again for a three count.
5) Cerebro Negro, Cyborg, Peligro b Freelance, Hammer, Tribal
## Peligro replaced Veneno, while Hammer filled in for Eterno (who might have been in IWRG instead.) Best and probably longest match of the show, with everyone but Hammer looking good (and he looked good when he was getting hit.) Rudos took it.
6) Heddi Karaoui b Jorge Macias [brazilian shoot fight]
## Jorge Macias replaced Zumbi, out with a bronchitis. Macias looked like they dragged him off the street, didn't even have gloves, and this was an umimpressive looking worked MMA battle full of pulled shots and each guy getting finishing submissions regularly. Heddi got the submission in the third of three minute rounds.
7) Fantasma de la Ópera, Mad Man Pondo, Zumbido b Ángel o Demonio, Súper Crazy, Tony Rivera
## Destroyer (Hilario) was helping Pondo thru the match. A crazy brawl. Pondo's team was bout to win, Los Porros ran in with barbed wire bats, ATM ran out to help Pondo's team, and Pondo put Angel o Demonio thru a table that was slightly on fire for the win. Post match antics included more light tubes broken, ligther fluid poured in eyes, and Tony and Zumbido trying to stir up interest for a hair match.

3) Corsario Negro, Kung Fu Jr., Sepulturero I vs Ccocolores, Coco Amarillo Jr., Coco Blanco

IWRG (SUN) 07/03/2011 Arena Naucalpan [http://alfilodelring.blogspot.com/2011/07/arena-naucalpan-3-de-julio-del-2011.html Al Filo del Ring, http://www.flickr.com/photos/blackterry/sets/72157627111666728/with/5899927325/ Black Terry Jr. (flickr), http://estrellasdelring.blogspot.com/2011/07/el-festival-de-mascaras-fue-un-festival.html Estrellas del Ring, http://www.fuegoenelring.com/articles_luchas_full.php?articles_id=2046 Fuego en el Ring]
** Festivals de las MascarasAttendance: 2000
1) Dinamic Black, Ray Marin b Alan Extreme, Muerte Infernal
## Ray Marin and Muerte Infernal were replacements for Nino Tormenta and Karibe King - those two are Fray Tormenta trainees, so probably the other two are as well.
2) Arácnido, Eterno, Jack b Capitán Muerte, El Hijo del Diablo, Fuego Eterno
## Freelance, Segura, Cerebro Negro and Dr. Cerebro were listed in this match. 3 of those guys were over in IWL. Fuego Eterno & Aracnido look like someone's trainees. First match here for Jack in a while.
3) Cuchillo, Kahoz, Rambo b Coco Rojo, El Brazo, Veneno
## Brazo replaced Bobby Lee Jr. Makes sense why Veneno worked the IWL opener now - he managed to get to both shows.
4) Fray Tormenta, Pantera, Solar I b Black Terry, Negro Navarro, Scorpió Jr.
## Tecnicos took 1/3. There was a bit with Pantera and the lucha commission over Pantera wearing his mask lately. Commissioner wanted him to take it off, Pantera pointed out this was the one show where he didn't have to.
5) Canek, Konnan, Rayo de Jalisco Jr. DQ Cien Caras, Máscara Año 2000, Universo 2000
## Canek was the surprise partner of Konnan and Rayo. Konnan was 'injured' early on, giving the rudos the advantage. Tecnicos eliminated Universo 2000, but he came back in for the DQ. Konnan returned to make the save, but actually turned on the tecnicos.

## There are new rules for the first two matches on these shows. Openers now have a ten minute time limit. If they reach a draw, it'll be up to the experts (Black Terry and ref Cavernas Torres) to pick the winner. They picked the rudos here.
2) Carta Brava Jr., Imposible, Keshin Black b Comando Negro, Dinamic Black, Golden Magic
## Comando Negro was a replacement for Freelance and is still flirting with the tecnico side. Segundas will now be one fall 15 minute time limit matches, with the same judges decisions for tie breakers. Carta Brava beat Comando Negro with one minute left to get the win.

Security took 911 to the back. Rudos won the first, tecnicos won the second. AK-47 was hurt on Angelico dive in the third. Veneno was about to finish Diablo, but Avisman and a new masked man ran in for the DQ. Diablo announced that the masked man was Kid USA, the new member of Los Gringos VIP. Golden Magic and Dinamic Black ran in for the save, and declared they were forming their own group, Los Revolucionarios.

## Pantera is still wearing his mask. The two agreed to a technical match. It didn't stay that way. Ultimo Gladiador own the first, Pantera took the second. Hijo del Diablo, second of Ultimo Gladiador, interfered to attack Pantera. Veneno, Pantera's second, tried to stop him and was ejected by the referee. Hijo del Diablo interfered again, was caught, and ejected. Pantera won with a top rope hurracanrana.
5) Pirata Morgan, Silver King DQ LA Park, Máscara Año 2000 Jr.
## Park was a tecnico tonight. Referee helped Pirata and Silver. They won 1 and 3, Pirata faking a foul from Park in the third.

CMLL (SUN) 07/17/2011 Arena Coliseo [http://estrellasdelring.blogspot.com/2011/07/grande-maestro-arkangel.html CMLL, http://lacatedraldelaluchalibre.blogspot.com/2011/07/25-aniversario-de-arkangel-flamite.html La Catedral]
** Arkangel 25th Anniversary Show
1) Starman b Camaleón, Halcón Mágico, Bobby Zavala, Kato, Trueno, Robin, Último Samurai (Guerrero), Warrior Steel, Cocolores, Trox, Flamita, Canelo Casas, Freesbe, Yago, Príncipe Azteca
## Referee was Teddy, an indy referee who works (or worked?) for Perros del Mal. Kind of a Royal Rumble style match, but with 2 new wrestlers every 90 seconds. Order of entry was Freesbee & Starman, Canelo Casas & Flamita, Trox & Cocolores, Warrior Steel & Ultimo Samurai, Robin & Trueno, Kato & Bobby Zavala, and Halcon Magico (not Super Halcon - this one turned up in 2006 IWRG teaming with Tiger Kid) & Camaleon. No one was eliminated until the ring filled up. Guys were eliminating themselves by doing dives, including Magico moonsaulting to the floor. Final three were Camaleon, Flamita and Starman, Starman dumping Flamita for the win. Cesar says Flamita and Warrior Steel looked good, and didn't like Robin and Cocolores comedy.
2) Dalis la Caribeña, Lady Afrodita b La Comandante, Mima Shimoda
## Lady Afrodita is an Arkangel trainee, making her CMLL debut and getting her first win. One fall basic match.
3) Dr. X, Hooligan, Loco Max, Nitro, Yoshihashi b Cancerbero, Euforia, Pólvora, Raziel, Virus [cibernetico]
## Absolutely no mention of what's become of Skandalo. Order of elimination was Yoshihashi (via Virus), Virus (Hooligan), Hooligan (Raziel), Polvora (Tuareg distracted the refs so Dr. X could toss his own mask to Polvora for the DQ, hmmm), Loco Max (Cancerbero), Raziel (Nitro), Nitro (Cancerbero). That left Dr. X alone against Cancerbero and Euforia, but he beat Euforia and then the big man to take copa home for the Tuareg.
4) Arkángel de la Muerte, Ephesto, Shigeo Okumura b Mr. Cacao, Stuka Jr., Valiente
## The Tuareg entered with Arkangel before the match, and Arkangel thanked everyone for supporting him. Rudos took 2/3. Arkangel pinned Mr. Cacao in the third fall for the win, then challenged for a mask match.
5) Delta, La Máscara, La Sombra DQ Atlantis, Mephisto, Volador Jr.
## No Toscano again, Delta replacing him. Tecnicos took 2/3. Mephisto fouled Sombra for the pin.

The Right was banned from ringisde. Sol was less absent here, running in at the end to help out Lizmark. They tossed Lizmark's cane to him, but Brewer got it and smacked Lizmark. Ref saw the cane, and called the DQ. No title change.
&& This taping sounds vastly entertaining. LLUSA announced Charlie Malice Jr. will debut on the next taping. Hmmmm. Not sure of the next taping (or when this might ever air, of course), but if you like to read the tea leaves, it's interesting to note they stopped using licensed music and went to using generic themes instead.

Dorian told Marisela he could not be fired and TNA was taking over. Sociedad celebrated the title win with Park angrily watching from afar, then threatened to beat up Wagner. Mesias ran down to run them off. Park made it clear he didn't like Wagner, didn't like Mesias and wasn't too fond of Jarrett or Konnan either.

## Another very bloody match, the third of the last four. Halloween was first out, followed by Monster and Murder. Damian told X-Fly to hold Psycho for a top rope move, and Damian climbed, and climbed, and climbed right to safety. That left the heavyweight champion of Mexico and Psycho Clown, and X-Fly was the big loser on this night.

After the Perros dominated for a while, Durok and Bestia did dive and Freeyser went for another chain punch. Damian ducked, and the referee Rubinksy got hit. Freeyzer tossed the chain to Damian, the other referee Toby spotted Damian with the chain and the referee down, and called for a DQ. The new Termerarios are now 2-0, and have not dropped a fall. Perros wanted a super libre rematch.

Damian noted he has "several commitments" left to AAA and other groups, but will retire after that match.

## Pimpi won, of course. Two short falls, one long fall. Orquidea fouled Pimpi and got a visual pin, but the ref would not count. Pimpi did the same and got the pin.

1) Ángel Azteca Jr., Molotov b Bobby Zavala, Disturbio
## Tecs took 1/3.
2) Misterioso II, Shigeo Okumura, Yoshihashi b Dragón Lee, Pegasso, Rey Cometa
## Rudos took 1/3.
3) Blue Panther, La Máscara, Rush b Felino, Hiroshi Tanahashi, Negro Casas
## Felino was honored for 25 years in wrestling (?) before the match with a video tribute. Puma, Tiger, Princesa Blanca and Dalis were among the group part of the pre-match celebration. Negro was out there too,, of course, and Panico is visible in the pictures. Felino thanked the crowd. Mascara and Tanahashi were the captains and exchanged the first two falls (Mascara taking the first.) Blue Panther and Rush beat Felino & Negro in the third. After the match, those two tecnicos made hair match challenges to the Casas brothers.
4) Volador Jr. b Máscara Dorada [lightning]
## Volador won clean via backcracker in 9 minutes.
5) Diamante b Pólvora [CMLL Universal, eightfinal]
## Matchups set up by a seeding battle royal. Diamante won via springboard 450, but seemed to suffer a left elbow injury.
6) La Sombra b Ángel de Oro [CMLL Universal, eightfinal]
## Backflip into a moonsault for the win. Angel de Oro offered a handshake before the match, but Sombra refused. Sombra offered a handshake after the match, but Angel de Oro angrily refused.
7) Rey Bucanero b Héctor Garza [CMLL Universal, eightfinal]
## less than a minute, Bucanero putting his feet on the ropes for the win. Garza challenged Bucanero to a hair match.
8) Mephisto b Ephesto [CMLL Universal, eightfinal]
## These two shook hands. Mephisto blocked the Ephesto Roll into his own cradle for the win.
9) La Sombra b Diamante [CMLL Universal, quarterfinal]
## Brillante Bomb to advance.
10) Rey Bucanero b Mephisto [CMLL Universal, quarterfinal]
## Bridging suplex.
11) La Sombra b Rey Bucanero [CMLL Universal, semifinal]
## Sombra finally kicked out of the Bucanero Destroyer (which beat him in the last big match between the two.) Felino, who was announcing, distracted Bucanero near the end of this one. Sombra Brillante Bombed Bucanero for the win. Sombra noted to the press that he's gotten a step further each year, and feels better prepared this year. Sombra isn't set on facing Lyger in the final, he just wants to win this. Sombra also said he does not expect to main event the anniversary show, because he's spent too much time in Japan to have built that sort of rivalry. Felino & Bucanero made hair match challenges again.
12) Dragón Rojo Jr., Último Guerrero  (c) b Atlantis, Guerrero Maya Jr. [CMLL TAG]
## This match did not start until after these shows usually end, and live reports mention people did leave before it was over. Guerrero Maya beat UG with the Mayan Sacrifice (?) and Atlantis got Dragon Rojo with a 'rana to take the first. Champs got pins to take the second and tie it up. In the third, Atlantis eliminated UG with the Atlantida. Dragon Rojo managed to beat Maya on his own. Atlantis got Dragon Rojo in a foul again, but UG snuck in and fouled him, allowing Dragon Rojo to reverse the pin and get the win to keep the titles. UG explained that he didn't teach Atlantis everything about being a rudo because he knew this day would come, and Dragon Rojo said the next goal was to get a mask match between Atlatnis and UG, though Delta & Maya would fall too if they got in the way.

AAA TV (SUN) 10/09/2011 Arena Monterrey, Monterrey, Nuevo León [http://estrellasdelring.blogspot.com/2011/10/los-psycho-circus-son-el-antirrabico-de.html Estrellas del Ring, PPV]
** Heroes Inmortales, 2011Attendance: 8000
1) Cinthia Moreno, Fabi Apache, Mari Apache b Jennifer Blake, Sexy Star, Velvet Sky [glow in the dark]
## Tough to follow match. Jennfier wrapped some tape around her arm, but Sexi Star's gear was the only glow in the dark material that showed up well. Sexi Star pinned Fabi after chair shots to the back, and the rudas danced in the ring after the match.
2) El Elegido, Octagoncito, Pimpinela Escarlata b Alan Stone, Mini Histeria, Polvo de Estrellas [lumberjack]
## usual strap match combined with usual Pimpi match. She submitted Alan Stone. After Elegido & Octagoncito left for no apparent reason, the exoticos attacked. Casandro returned to make the save.
3) Abyss, Chessman  (c) b Extreme Tiger, Jack Evans [AAA TAG, TLC]
## Good match for this sort of thing. Tiger did his guillotine legdrop off a ladder onto Chessman. Rudos rallied, Abyss chokeslammed Tiger thru a table with tacks on it, and Chessman put Jack thru another table before grabbing the belts. New Champs.
4) Electroshock b La Parka, Brutus Magnus, Joe Lider, Zorro, Jeff Jarrett, LA Park, Cibernético, Silver King [Copa Antonio Pena]
## Heavy Metal did not appear; he may have been on La Acedemia instead. Royal Rumble rules. Parka and Park started, followed by Silver King, Electroshock, Cibernetico. La Parka eliminated himself and Cibernetico and those two fought to the back. Zorro came in, with his stick in play. Jeff Jarrett followed, and Silver King was thrown out. Joe Lider was in next, then Magnus. Park dropkicked Zorro out. Electro lowbridged Magnus to send him out. LA Park monkey fliped Lider off the apron to eliminate him. Jarrett and Park beat up on Electro forever, but when park went to pose on the middle rope, Park tossed him. Jarrett had a fit, then later tried to pull Park off the apron. Park fought him off, but a Masked Zorro ran in to attack, and Electroshock threw him out for the win.
5) El Mesías NC Sting
## Sting was promoted as Classic Sting, instead appeared as Joker Sting. Short match. Jarrett led the TNA guys to ringside. Brutus offered a chair, but Sting hit him instead. TNA guys all beat up Sting, Sting and Mesias ran them off. No DQ for any of this, and Mesias and Sting shook hands and posed to end it. No finish, bad match otherwise.
6) Dr. Wagner Jr.  (c) b el Hijo del Perro Aguayo [AAA LA, bull terrier]
## Octagon & Konnan Big were the seconds, with Silver King wandering out to join in too. Silver and Konnan got involved a lot. Octagon stood around and argued a bit. Expected brawl. Rudos dominated early, Wagner came back while taking off his chain so he could do his dive. Wagner got the chain back around and, after some near falls, hit all six corners for the win. After the match, Octagon came in the ring, and hit Wagner with a chair! La Parka ran down for the save, but he also turned on Wagner. Wagner was totally destroyed, and Konnan announced Parka & Octagon as new members of La Sociedad. They did look skinnier than usual, and they may be setting up a reveal that they're fakes just like Masked Zorro (which would be overdoing it by two), but the implication here was they were the real Parka & Octagon.
7) Monster Clown, Murder Clown, Psycho Clown b Damián 666, Halloween, Nicho el Millionario [cage, mask, hair]
## Advertised as a dome cage match, but took place in the usual six side cage. Mini Clown got in the match to start, and took a piledriver. He was up and fighting five minutes later. Order of escape was Mini Clown, Murder Clown, Halloween & Monster escaped somewhere in here, Bestia came in, Bestia left, Joe Lider came in (he'd been stretchered out of the Copa Pena match) to attack Nicho, Bestia came back in to help, Lider destroyed him, Psycho tried to leave, Perros stopped him, Bestia left again, Damian left with him, Lider set up Nicho on a table, Psycho jumped off the top of the cage with a spash, and both Lider and Psycho left for the win. All three Perros (but not Bestia) were shaved. Nicho was strechered out.

Pirata attacked the shoulder, Trauma "withstood the attack stoically". Pirata put Trauma in his own hold, but he got the ropes. Trauma I put Pirata in the cruceta invertida himself, Pirata got the ropes, Trauma got the hold a second time, and Pirata gave up.
5) Oficial 911, Oficial AK47, Oficial Fierro b Demente Extreme, Súper Mega, Violento Jack
## IWRG vs DTU. DTU brought chairs and light tubes to the match, but the Oficales insisted they give them up because this was to be a clean match. It stayed that way for the first few exchanges, but Violento Jack reverted and hit AK47 with a chair for the first fall DQ. Usual DTU match from there, but DQs were still called - Oficials lost the second fall when AK-47 put light tubes on Jack and hit them with a chair. Bloody mask ripping third. Violento Jack tried to Martinete AK-47, but the referee broke it up. Jack tried a rana on AK47, but AK47 killed him with a move for the win. Rematch was agreed for next week.

** Castillo del Terror, 2011

## Ten minute fight before people start to leave. Order of exit was Zumbi, Spartan, Super Nova, Carta Braa Jr., Machin, Hijo de La park and Hijo de Mascara Ano 2000. That left 911, Golden Magic and King Drako. Rudos teamed up on Magic, but 911 betrayed Drako and left him behind. Drako tried to do flying moves against Golden Magic, that backfired, and Golden Magic left to win. King Drako, the least known guy in the cage, is Mateo Alcantara Villafuerte, from DF, 18 years a wrestler. He gave the same name back <a href=http://www.thecubsfan.com/cmll/?p=1868>in 2007 when he was unmasked as as Halcon Salvaje</a>.

AAA TV (SAT) 11/05/2011 Centro Civico Nueva Aragon, Ecatepec, Estado de México [http://luchalibreaaa.com/en-ecatepec-se-consuma-la-venganza-de-octagon.php AAA]Attendance: 4500
1) Argenis, Daga, Relámpago b Decnnis, Tigre Cota, Tito Santana
## Daga, last seen here as part of team IWRG, replaced Atomic Boy, Tiger Cota replaced Mortiz. Argenis pinned Cota for the win.
2) Cassandro, El Brazo, Pimpinela Escarlata b Nygma, Pasion Kristal, Yuriko
## Casandro was announced for this match, then pulled from the match, then wrestled in the match as a surprise. El Brazo wrestled as La Braza. Casandro pinned Nygma for the win.
3) Aerostar, Fénix, Sugi San b Dark Dragón, La Parka, Súper Fly
## Sugi reappeared to replace Drago. Parka dominated the tecnicos, but Aerostar got Super Fly with a 'rana for the win. La Sociedad hit the ring after the match. Konnan talked about Antonio Pena calling Octagon and Konnan first when he decided to call AAA (which is the real story.) Konnan said Pena had promised to one day give Octagon and Konnan shares in the company, but the Roldans never lived up to the promise. Konnan stripped Super Fly of his Milicia leadership for this latest failure, and appointed Octagon as the new leader. Octagon reminded the crowd of his promise to strike back at everyone who's done his wrong, and ordered the Milicia to destroy Super Fly. They did, utterly massacring Super Fly. Recap notes this is the same building where Super Fly took out Octagon earlier this year.
4) Chessman, Octagón b Dr. Wagner Jr., Electroshock
## LA Park interfered, setting up Chessman sneaking in a foul on Wagner, and Octagon grabbed the pin. The Milicia was out with Octagon and also getting involved in the match.
5) Damián 666, LA Park b El Mesías, Zorro
## Park beat Zorro with a powerbomb. Wagner ran out for Park after the match, Octagon ran out after him, and Zorro made the save. Zorro reaffirmed he's part of AAA.
&& After the opener, Joaquin Roldan (w/Mesias, Electroshock, Zorro, Aerostar, Fenix) responded to Octagon and Parka's reasons for teaming. One of Parka's reasons had been AAA sending Ozz & Cuervo to Japan to stop them from helping him against the Bizarros, but Roldan pointed out those two had won the AJPW tag team titles. Roldan pointed out Parka could've teamed up with any of the other guys in the ring, but Parka refused. Joaquin says AAA will continue to be #1 with or without Parka. Konnan and Dorian came to the ring to mock the Mexican fans for doing the "You can't see me" and counting in english.

Garza appears to be treated completely normal here, even picking up a pin on Mephisto in the second fall. 1/3 for the rudos. Volador won with a backcracker on Super Porky. I don't know how he did that and lived.
5) Rush  (c) b Terrible [CMLL LH]
## As usual, Dragon Lee was his brother's second. Terrible's old ally Averno was his second. Terrible took the first, Rush suffering a knee injury in the process. Rush still managed to take a short second fall. Rush won with the same piledriver move he used versus Yoshishashi.

1) Mini Histeria, Tigre Cota b Argenis, Máscarita Divina
2) Dark Dragón, Tito Santana b Sugi San, Súper Fly
## Moved down a spot to the second match. Super Fly was taken out by Octagon & the rudos walking to the ring. Sugi was left on his own for a while. Super Fly did recover to help make the comeback, but the rudos still won. Sugi got dropped on his head on a 'rana-like move from Dark Dragon and was strechered out.

## Casandro pinned Yuriko
4) Abyss, Chessman b Extreme Tiger, Joe Lider
## Moved down a spot to the fourth match. Lider looked like he might win the match, and Nicho ran in to put a stop to that. Abyss put Lider thru a table for the win. Nicho threw fire in Tiger's face.
5) Gunner b Monster Clown
## Also moved down a spot. This was a bit weird. Mesias came out first, showing an elbow injury, explaining he'd been attacked by Gunner and saying the medical personal did not want him to wrestle but he did want to anyway. Konnan came out, and ordered Mesias to fight Dark Dragon & Tito to get to Mesias. That did not last long before Gunner jumped in. Monster Clown, Murder Clown and Joaquin Roldan came out for the save, with Roldan making the actual match Monster Clown vs Gunner. Plenty of of interference and Gunner won.
6) Fénix, Jack Evans b el Hijo del Perro Aguayo, Halloween
## Moved up two spots. Rudos dominated the match, but Jack again snuck a pin on Perro via moonsault on chair for the win. Perros were very displeased, blooding Jack after the match. No new Perro.
7) Dr. Wagner Jr., Psycho Clown, Zorro DQ LA Park, Nicho el Millionario, Octagón
## Dr. Wagner was accompanied by Hijo de Dr. Wagner, who was attacked by Park during the match. Octagon had Tito & Dark Dragon fighting for him. After a brawl, Octagon fouled Wagner for the DQ. Park vs Wagner for Guerra de Titanes was announced. Hijo del Dr. Wagner will be Wagner's second for that match.

## Hector Garza replaced Halloween, who was healthy enough to run in the last match but had a taped midsection here. Jack 630 senton'd Dragon to continue his winning streak versus the Perros. Perro Jr. gave Jack a chair shot, leaving him bloody again. Drago returned to make the save, including blowing the mist at Dark Dragon.

## No Dark Dragon (mist!), but Konnan and LA Park and Octagon's sticks all helped him foul Super Fly for the win. Joaquin turned up after the match to declare NEW RULES: every time the the luchadors yelled at Marisela Pena, run-in a match, or break equipment, he was going to fine Konnan $50,000. LA Park immediately broke a monitor. Konnan was very concerned. Park is awesome.

## Mini Clown was with the Psycho Circus. Murder pinned Gladiador.
6) LA Park, La Parka b Dr. Wagner Jr., Electroshock
## Earlier in the night, after the second match, Dorian, Konnan, Parka & Octagon appeared in the ctner of the ring. Dorian announced La Sociedad had a new member - Cibernetico. Parka was very unhappy, but Dorian explained it was business. Konnan wasn't high on this idea either, saying Cibernetico offered to join them last year if they'd bring back Charly Manson, but only used them. (???) Dorian promised to make everything work. In this match, Parka pinned Electro with his feet on the ropes. Joaquin came out after the match to yell at Parka. Cibernetico finally appeared here, with a chair, and Octagon ordered him to hit Joaquin. Cibernetico instead attacked La Sociedad. Perros ran in to beat him down. The Psycho Circus made the save, but Cibernetico and Joaquin Roldan were stretchered out.

Wagner recovered, Octagon attacked him, Wagner took him out, and Park used the distraction to hit Wagner with knucks for the pin and the title. Park was joined by Toscano, Texano, and Mascara Ano 2000 Jr. as psuedo-CMLL faction. They all beat up the Wagners until the Clowns made the save.

AAA TV (TUE) 12/20/2011 Plaza de Toros Belisario Arteaga, Chilpancingo, Guerrero [http://www.mediotiempo.com/mas-deportes/lucha-libre/noticias/2011/12/21/el-consejo-volvio-a-atacar-a-aaa AAA]
1) Máscarita Dorada, Octagoncito b Mini Histeria, Mini Psicosis
2) La Braza, Pimpinela Escarlata b Jennifer Blake, La Hechicera, Sexy Star
## Inexplicably a handicap match. Casandro was supposed to be on the tecnico side and was replaced by La Braza, but La Hechicera was also added to the ruda side. Maybe Hechicera was there to lose; Brazo splashed her for the win.
3) Argenis, Atomic Boy, Fénix b Dark Dragón, Tigre Cota, Tito Santana
## Tecnicos won via Fenix flying double knee to Dark Dragon. El Consejo (Toscano, Terrible and Mascara Ano 2000) ran out, attacked the tecnicos, and left thru the crowd.
4) Nicho el Millionario b Joe Lider
## Seconds were Tiger Cota and Jack Evans, but Perro and Hector got involved by the end. Nicho got the win, and Lider challenged him to a no-referee cage match with the loser losing their hair. Nicho seemed to have no problem with that idea.
5) Monster Clown, Murder Clown, Psycho Clown b Chessman, Halloween, Súper Fly
## Prior to the fourth match, Konnan, LA Park, Chessman and Jennifer had all come to the ring to brag about La Sociedad having all the titles but the cruiserweight one. (Gotta trick Jack into defending it, somehow.) Joaquin interrupted the party to point out Konnan was now up to 250K in fines after Guerra de Titanes. They weren't specified, but this is probably the run-ins and harassing Marisela again. Joaquin also wanted to know if Konnan was responsible for El Consejo. It doesn't sound like Konnan really answered, because he was interested in a different question - why did El Consejo not attack LA Park? LA Park told Konnan to figure out. Segment ended with Dorian, Joaquin, LA Park and Konnan all claiming no responsibility for Consejo, but Konnan being sure that one of them was lying. Super Fly refused to work with his partners in this match. Halloween turned on him with a piledriver, and the Clowns pinned Fly for the loss. El Consejo ran in again after the match, attacking the Clowns, then surprising the rudos by attacking them as well. They escaped thru the crowd again.
6) El Mesías, Jack Evans b el Hijo del Perro Aguayo, Héctor Garza
## Garza was the "surprise" Perro. Jack again pinned Perro by surprise.
7) LA Park, Octagón DQ Dr. Wagner Jr., Extreme Tiger
## Wagner hit Tirantes for the DQ. El Consejo hit the ring a third time after the match, attacking Wagner, Tiger and Octagon, with Park staying far away. La Sociedad and AAA both ran out to drive Consejo off, but the two sides did not get along with each other. Texano got a microphone long enough to declare El Consejo the only world class luchadors and promised more members to join them.

IWRG (THU) 12/22/2011 Arena Naucalpan [http://www.flickr.com/photos/blackterry/sets/72157628534759167/?page=2 Black Terry Jr. (flickr), http://estrellasdelring.blogspot.com/2011/12/el-trauma-i-destapa-al-oficial-ak-47.html Estrellas del Ring, http://www.thegladiatores.com/?p=7246 The Gladiatores]
** 34th Arena Naucalpan AnniversaryAttendance: 2400
1) Gemelo Fantástico I, Gemelo Fantástico II, Imposible b Astro de Plata, Astro Rey Jr., Tritón
## Gemelos win in straight fall, continuing their hot streak.
2) Alan Extreme, Apolo Estrada Jr., Avisman b Centvrión, Multifacético, Saruman
## Quick match. Apolo defeated Multifacetico with a hand on the ropes. They were both bleeding by the end, and challenged to a hair match for 01/01.
3) Carta Brava Jr. b Dinamic Black  (c) [IWRG IC Light]
## Carta Brava took 2/3 to win the title. Dinamic Black hurt his hip in a dive in the third fall, which played into the finish. Said to be a great match.
4) Eterno  (c) b Golden Magic  (c) [IWRG IC WELTER, WWS WELTER]
## Golden Magic was IWRG champ, Eterno was WWS. Originally promoted as unification match, but both titles may be kept now. Eterno took falls 2/3 to win the IWRG title, winning via top rope styles clash. Another well regarded match.
5) Canis Lupus, Head Hunter I, Hernandez b Pantera, Texano Jr., Tony Rivera
## Negro Navarro was replaced by Hernandez, who earlier had said on Twitter he was in Mexico on vacation and to catch up with old friend Head Hunter I. Tony Rivera replaced Toscano, who can't seem to make it to any IWRG show he's scheduled. Rudos took 1/3, with Lupus again challenging Pantera for a Rey del Ring shot.
6) Oficial 911, Trauma II b Oficial AK47, Trauma I [relevos suicidas]
## Originally teased as Oficials vs Traumas in a double mask match, but instead was announced in this style. This portion was a single fall to the finish. Neither team felt much like working together, even to the point of the Oficals breaking up Traumas holds, even their partners. Both Traumas and Oficials faced off at points in the match. 911 took out Trauma I with a chair shot to eliminated him, then both Oficials attacked Trauma II. AK47 eventually hit his own partner by mistake, and Trauma II rolled up AK47 for the win.
7) Trauma I DQ Oficial AK47 [mask]
## This was a three fall bout, with the previous wrestlers as seconds. Majority of the crowd backed the Traumas. In the first, 911 hit Trauma I with a chair shot again, and AK-47 gave Trauma a Devil's Wings for the win. AK-47 missed a top rope move in the second, and Trauma I submitted him to a inverted figure four. Both men bleed in the final fall. 911 pulled out ref El Grillo on a near fall. Grillo was distracted later by both seconds, allowing AK-47 to drop Trauma I with a martinete. AK-47 covered, and Grillo counted the pin even while a doctor had already slid in the ring to check on Trauma I. AK-47 was declared the winner for a minute or so before Grillo saw the condition Trauma was in, deduced AK-47 must've given him a martinete, and overturned his own call for the DQ. Fans were massively unhappy when it appeared AK-47 was going to win via the martinete, throwing garbage at the ring, and were okay with the over turned finish. Oficial AK-47 is Mario Pardo Villagómez, from Casas Grandes, Chihuahua, 26 years old, 7 years a luchador. Trauma I, stretchered out with a destroyed mask, still managed to dedicate the win to his mom and the fans.
&& Believed to be a sell out.

## Taboo was the champion. Taboo & Electroshock tried to fight together to stop Head Hunter, but failed. Head Hunter won the title. Electroshock gave him credit for a win, but asked for a shot.
6) La Parka Jr., Octagón  (c) b Chessman, Silver King [MEX TAG, cage]
## Silver King and La Parka escaped first. Octagon was next. Silver had a glass of beer ready to throw in Octagon's face, but Octagon avoided and Chessman took it. Parka pulled Silver King and Octagon escaped to keep the titles.
